bes.com: Forbes World's Richest People 2004|date=28 April 2006|website=Web.archive.org|accessdate=25 October 2017}}</ref>\n| 587, Richest: Bill Gates $46.6 billion {{flagicon|United States}}\n|-\n| 2005\n| 1: Oprah Winfrey $1.3 billion {{flagicon|United States}}\n| 2: \n*Michael Lee-Chin $2.5 billion {{flagicon|Jamaica}}{{flagicon|Canada}}\n*Mohammad Al Amoud $2.5 billion {{flagicon|Ethiopia}}{{flagicon|Saudi Arabia}}\n| 691, Richest: Bill Gates $46.5 billion{{flagicon|United States}}\n|-\n| 2006\n| 1: Oprah Winfrey $1.4 billion{{flagicon|United States}}\n| 2: \n*Mohammad Al Amoudi $6.9 billion {{flagicon|Ethiopia}}{{flagicon|Saudi Arabia}}\n* Michael Lee-Chin $2.1 billion{{flagicon|Jamaica}}{{flagicon|Canada}}<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2006/10/7TE8.html | title=#365 Michael Lee-Chin|work=Forbes}}</ref>\n| 793, Richest: Bill Gates $50 billion{{flagicon|United States}}\n|-\n| 2007\n| 2: \n*[[Oprah Winfrey]] $1.5 billion {{flagicon|United States}}\n* Bob Johnson $1.1 billion{{flagicon|United States}}<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/10/07billionaires_Robert-Johnson_VYCO.html | work=Forbes | title=#840 Robert Johnson | date=2007-03-08}}</ref>\n|2: \n*Mohammad Al Amoudi $8 billion{{flagicon|Ethiopia}}{{flagicon|Saudi Arabia}}\n*Michael Lee-Chin $1.6 billion{{flagicon|Canada}}{{flagicon|Jamaica}}<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/10/07billionaires_Michael-Lee-Chin_7TE8.html | work=Forbes | title=#618 Michael Lee-Chin | date=2007-03-08}}</ref>\n| 946, Richest: Bill Gates $56 billion{{flagicon|United States}}\n|-\n| 2008\n| 5: \n*[[Aliko Dangote]] $3.3 billion {{flagicon|Nigeria}}\n*Oprah Winfrey $2.5 billion {{flagicon|United States}}<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2008/10/billionaires08_Oprah-Winfrey_O0ZT.html | work=Forbes | title=#462 Oprah Winfrey | date=2008-03-05}}</ref>\n*[[Patrice Motsepe]] $2.4 billion {{flagicon|South Africa}}<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2008/10/billionaires08_Patrice-Motsepe_RS9H.html | work=Forbes | title=#503 Patrice Motsepe | date=2008-03-05}}</ref>\n*[[Mo Ibrahim]] $2.5 billion {{flagicon|Sudan}}{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2008/10/billionaires08_Mohammed-Ibrahim_IK9A.html | work=Forbes | title=#462 Mohammed Ibrahim | date=2008-03-05}}</ref>\n*Bob Johnson $1 billion {{flagicon|United States}} <ref name=\"#1062 Robert Johnson\" />\n|2: Mohammad Al Amoudi $9 billion{{flagicon|Ethiopia}}{{flagicon|Saudi Arabia}}\nMichael Lee-Chin $1.8 billion{{flagicon|Jamaica}}{{flagicon|Canada}}<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2008/10/billionaires08_Michael-Lee-Chin_7TE8.html | work=Forbes | title=#677 Michael Lee-Chin | date=2008-03-05}}</ref>\n| 1,125, Richest: Warren Buffett $62 billion{{flagicon|United States}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| 5:\n*Oprah Winfrey $2.7 billion {{flagicon|United States}} \n*[[Aliko Dangote]] $2.5 billion {{flagicon|Nigeria}}\n*[[Mo Ibrahim]] $2 billion {{flagicon|Sudan}}{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}\n*[[Femi Otedola]] $1.6 billion {{flag icon|Nigeria}}\n*Patrice Motsepe $1.3 billion {{flag icon|South Africa}}\n|2: Mohammad Al Amoudi $9 billion{{flagicon|Ethiopia}}{{flagicon|Saudi Arabia}}\nMichael Lee-Chin $1 billion{{flagicon|Jamaica}}{{flagicon|Canada}}<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2009/10/billionaires-2009-richest-people_Michael-Lee-Chin_7TE8.html | work=Forbes | title=#701 Michael Lee-Chin - The World's Billionaires 2009 | date=2009-03-11}}</ref>\n|793, Richest: Bill Gates $40 billion{{flagicon|United States}}\n|-\n| 2010 \n| 4: \n*Oprah Winfrey $2.4 billion {{flagicon|United States}}\n*Patrice Motsepe $2.3 billion {{flag icon|South Africa}}\n*[[Adam Sedik]] $2.1 billion{{flagicon|Nigeria}}\n*[[Mo Ibrahim]] $2 billion {{flagicon|Sudan}}{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}\n|2: Mohammad Al Amoudi $10 billion{{flagicon|Ethiopia}}{{flagicon|Saudi Arabia}}\nMichael Lee-Chin $1 billion{{flagicon|Jamaica}}{{flagicon|Canada}}<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2010/10/billionaires-2010_Michael-Lee-Chin_7TE8.html | work=Forbes | title=#937 Michael Lee-Chin | date=2010-03-10}}</ref>\n| 1,011, Richest: [[Carlos Slim Helu]] & family $53.5 billion<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbes.com/2010/03/10/worlds-richest-people-slim-gates-buffett-billionaires-2010_land.html|archiveurl=http://archive.today/20120918131508/http://www.forbes.com/2010/03/10/worlds-richest-people-slim-gates-buffett-billionaires-2010_land.html|url-status=dead|title=The World's Billionaires|editor= Luisa Kroll|editor2= Matthew Miller|website=Forbes|archivedate=2012-09-18}}</ref> {{flagicon|Mexico}}\n|-\n|2011\n| 5:\n*[[Aliko Dangote]] $13.8 billion {{flagicon|Nigeria}}<ref name=\"thenationonlineng.net\"/>\n* Patrice Motsepe $3.3 billion {{flag icon|South Africa}}\n* Oprah Winfrey $2.7 billion {{flagicon|United States}}\n* Mo Ibrahim $1.8 billion {{flagicon|Sudan}}{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} <ref name=\"forbes.com\" />\n* [[Mike Adenuga]] $2 billion{{flagicon|Nigeria}} <ref name=\"thenationonlineng.net\" /> \n|1: Mohammad Al Amoudi $12.3 billion{{flagicon|Ethiopia}}{{flagicon|Saudi Arabia}}\n|1,210, Richest: [[Carlos Slim Helu]] & family $74 billion{{flagicon|Mexico}}\n|-\n|2012 <ref name=\"Nsehe\">{{cite news| url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/mfonobongnsehe/2012/03/07/the-black-billionaires-2012/ |title=The Black Billionaires 2012| work=Forbes |date=March 7, 2012| first=Mfonobong | last=Nsehe}}</ref>\n| 5:\n*[[Aliko Dangote]] $11.2 billion {{flagicon|Nigeria}}<ref name=\"thenationonlineng.net\">{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110316115034/http://thenationonlineng.net/web3/news/30610.html|title=The Nation - Are Dangote and Adenuga truly Nigeria\u2019s richest men?|date=16 March 2011|accessdate=25 October 2017}}</ref>\n*Mike Adenuga $4.3 billion {{flagicon|Nigeria}} <ref name=\"thenationonlineng.net\" />\n* Patrice Motsepe $2.7 billion {{flag icon|South Africa}}\n* Oprah Winfrey $2.7 billion{{fla